The paper deals with the problem of recovering two unknown vectors from their circular convolution, which is a problem commonly studied in the information theory (cs.IT) and signal processing (cs.SP) communities. The approach taken in the paper involves convex programming, which is a popular technique in machine learning (cs.LG) and computer vision (cs.CV) for solving optimization problems. The paper also discusses the use of random subspaces, which is a topic studied in the field of statistical inference (cs.SI).
